{# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   /calculators — Pathway A v2: calculators gallery

   Restructured from a 5-tile text-list into a polished gallery that
   functions as the canonical entry point for every interactive
   calculator on the site. JM's framing: 'each tile shows an actual
   live thumbnail of the tool's heart (mini heatmap, mini chart, mini
   retirement curve…) with an Open button.' v1 shipped one live
   preview (Heatmap) as proof-of-concept. v2 expanded to 7 live
   renderers in calculators-minis.js. The page nav label was also
   renamed Tools → Calculators in commit 132f79a / 0148ba3.

   Hierarchy:
   - Featured row (2 tiles, large): The Bitcoin Retirement (live mini
     retirement curve) + Bitcoin vs. The Stock Market (live mini
     3-line wealth chart). These are the two highest-leverage
     personal-decision tools.
   - Tools grid (9 tiles, 3-col on desktop): the remaining
     Numbers-tier calculators plus the two Arguments-tier interactive
     ones (Half-Life, Melting Ice Cube).

   History note: through commit 0148ba3 the featured row paired the
   Heatmap with BvSM. The Heatmap is not strictly a calculator (no
   inputs that drive outputs — it's a static visualization grid),
   and with The Gallery now serving as the visual-showcase surface,
   it's better-suited there. The Bitcoin Retirement took its
   featured slot in commit (this one) — the live mini renderer
   already existed in calculators-minis.js for it.

   Notes for future iterations:
   - Live preview pattern is established by #mini-heatmap →
     calculators-minis.js → renderMiniHeatmap. Adding more live
     previews (mini-bvsm-chart, mini-retirement-curve, mini-power-
     law-channel, etc.) follows the same shape: add a target div
     in the tile markup, write a renderer in calculators-minis.js.
   - SP500_TR_DATA is duplicated between calculators-minis.js and
     bitcoin-vs-the-stock-market.js. Marked 'TR-SYNC' in both
     files. Future cleanup: extract to shared/comparator-data.js.
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}

